description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The opportunity has arisen for a Respiratory Physiologist to become an integral part of a highly motivated, friendly and enthusiastic team in the Lung Function Department at Homerton Hospital, London. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Our service provides a wide range of respiratory physiological studies including routine lung function tests, bronchial challenge testing, exercise tests, sleep studies, capillary blood gas analysis and allergy testing. We are also rapidly developing sleep and ventilation services. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The successful candidate should have effective communication and team working skills. They should also be self-motivated and willing to have a flexible approach to work. The candidate should have good science grounding and possess a BSc / NVQ level 3 clinical physiology (respiratory) or equivalent in Physiological Measurement (Respiratory Physiology).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Working Hours: 37.5 hours per week&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This post is for a 1 year Fixed Term contract with the possibility of extension&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Interview Date: TBC&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Rama Gorrela&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Sr Chief Respiratory Physiologist&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: rama.gorrela@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 0208-510-7803&lt;/p&gt;
